fr.sii.ogham.core.builder.configurer

Enum ConfigurationPhase

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ConfigurationPhase>
      • fr.sii.ogham.core.builder.configurer.ConfigurationPhase
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<ConfigurationPhase>

    public enum ConfigurationPhase
extends Enum<ConfigurationPhase>
    Enumeration for Ogham configuration phases for auto-configuration lifecycle:
    1. MessagingBuilder instantiation (using MessagingBuilder.standard() or MessagingBuilder.minimal()).
    2. Search MessagingConfigurer classes in the classpath and register found classes ordered by higher priority.
    3. Trigger AFTER_INIT phase: Instantiate and configure previously registered Configurers (only configurers registered for AFTER_INIT phase).
    4. Developer can configure Ogham using MessagingBuilder instance.
    5. Developer has finished configuring Ogham so he calls MessagingBuilder.build().
    6. Trigger BEFORE_BUILD phase: Instantiate and configure previously registered Configurers (only configurers registered for BEFORE_BUILD phase).
    7. Instantiate MessagingService according to MessagingBuilder configuration.
    8. Developer gets an instance of MessagingService completely configured.
    Author:

    See Also:
    ConfigurerFor, MessagingBuilder.register(MessagingConfigurer, int, ConfigurationPhase)

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • AFTER_INIT

        public static final ConfigurationPhase AFTER_INIT
        Early configuration phase.

        Property values provided by developer are not available because this phase is executed immediately when calling MessagingBuilder.standard() or MessagingBuilder.minimal(). PropertiesBuilder.set(String, String) used to set property values from code is called after.

        WARNING: Configuration set at this phase may not be overridable by developer.

      • BEFORE_BUILD

        public static final ConfigurationPhase BEFORE_BUILD
        Configuration applied just before building MessagingService.

        At this time, all property values can be safely used.

        Any configuration set at this phase has lower priority than any configuration provided by developer or configuration initialized during AFTER_INIT phase.
